tistical estimate of effect","To assess the methodological quality of studies","To evaluate the cost-effectiveness of interventions"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Escoping review maps the key concepts and available evidence in a research area\u003C/strong\u003E. It is particularly useful when examining broad topics or areas where the literature is complex and heterogeneous. Scoping reviews help identify research gaps and clarify key concepts.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDetermining the effectiveness of specific interventions\u003C/strong\u003E is more appropriately addressed through systematic reviews and meta-analyses that focus on specific research questions.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGenerating pooled statistical estimates\u003C/strong\u003E is the purpose of meta-analyses, which combine data from multiple studies to produce overall effect sizes.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAssessing methodological quality of studies\u003C/strong\u003E is typically performed in systematic reviews, whereas scoping reviews generally do not include quality assessment.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEvaluating cost-effectiveness\u003C/strong\u003E requires specific economic evaluations or targeted systematic reviews that focus on economic outcomes.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EScoping reviews follow a systematic approach to identify and map evidence, but differ from systematic reviews in that they aim to provide an overview of the available literature rather than answer a specific research question or assess study quality.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A scoping review maps the key concepts and types of evidence available in a research area.","Scoping reviews are useful when a topic is broad or complex, or when there is 